text: It's funny how we can still remember small details of past events in our lives. Moments that made us smile, laugh, cry and moments that first ignited the feeling of admiration to a person in our hearts. Moments that will forever be remembered.

author: 金杰瑞 𝙹𝚎𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚢
text: We exchanged messages here and there but one moment I can vividly remember was Christmas of that same year. I tried sending him a Christmas Greeting but the network was congested with text messages from everyone also sending their holiday cheers. The bane of the early 2000s.

author: 金杰瑞 𝙹𝚎𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚢
text: Upon knowing that me and some of my classmates were in his school, he tried finding me and saw me eating lunch at their huge canteen. We exchange phone numbers, I gave her my sister's number and he gave me his father's. Remember we neither own mobile phones that time.

author: 金杰瑞 𝙹𝚎𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚢
text: Weeks passed and I eventually got the chance to see him again when we were invited to Ateneo for some kind of event that I no longer remember. We had no communication prior given that elementary students owning a mobile phone wasn't as common back then.

author: 金杰瑞 𝙹𝚎𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚢
text: All good things must come to and end so did that memorable day. He made such a strong impression on me that I even cried at times thinking about just being able to spend one day with him. Proof of that is his name immortalized by yours truly on one our walls at home.

author: 金杰瑞 𝙹𝚎𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚢
text: In one of the games we played that day I was frustrated and impatient about not being able to win. He then patted my shoulder and said "Patience is a virtue". I first heard this famous saying from him and it stuck with me.

author: 金杰瑞 𝙹𝚎𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚢
text: Knowing the activity beforehand, his mom made an extra lunchbox for me and inside was a good serving of steamed rice and many pieces of tender juicy mini hotdogs. I always go home for lunch but it was a good change to stay in school and have lunch with him.

author: 金杰瑞 𝙹𝚎𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚢
